Daniel Sturridge is closing in on a return to the Liverpool side, where he hopes he can end Mario Balotelli's barren spell by striking up a partnership with the misfiring Italian.

The Reds striker posted a picture on Instagram of the pair pointing at each other, accompanied by the caption: 'My man!!! We're gonna be linking up soon!!'

Sturridge has not played for his club since a 3-0 win over Tottenham in August after injuring his thigh on international duty and has only recently returned to Merseyside after treatment in the US.

