Despite the  recent resurgence at Anfield, Brendan Rodgers' side has struggled for goals - especially from their strikers with Rickie Lambert and Fabio Borini netting only three league goals between them all season.

Balotelli has not scored a goal in the Premier League since his £16million move from AC Milan in the summer, although Rodgers has ruled out selling the 24-year-old in January.

The manager will be hoping that playing as a foil to Sturridge will help the Italian firebrand rediscover his touch, although Rodgers is determined not to rush the England international back.

Speaking last week, Rodgers said: ‘Daniel Sturridge is back and working well. Obviously he’s not ready to play as of yet but hopefully he’ll be ready in the near future.

